'''Unkanji-niimasu Naramoto Shrine''' (うんかんじにいますならもとじんじゃ) is a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|WD=Q134917286}} located in Nashimoto, {{ill|lt=Nara Prefecture|Q131287|WD=Q131287|1=Nara Prefecture}}{{ill|lt=Ikoma District|Q971003|WD=Q971003|1=Ikoma District, Nara}}{{ill|lt=Heguri Town|Q1346790|WD=Q1346790|1=Heguri, Nara}}. Under the {{ill|lt=Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines|Q712534|WD=Q712534|lt=former shrine ranking|1=Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines}}, it was classified as a {{ill|lt=Village shrine|Q134917284|WD=Q134917284|1=Son-sha}} and is a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=shrine receiving offerings of sacred food and heihaku|1=UNKNOWN}}.

=== Overview ===
In volume five of the {{ill|lt=Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|Q1052981|WD=Q1052981|WD=Q1052981|lt=Sandai Jitsuroku|1=Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku}}, it is recorded: “On the twenty-second day of the tenth month of the third year of {{ill|lt=Jōgan (Japan)|Q1075635|WD=Q1075635|lt=Jōgan|1=Jōgan}} (abridged), Unkanji, unranked Naramoto Shrine, was granted Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade.”

The former shrine site was the {{ill|lt=guardian shrine|Q13479654|WD=Q13479654|1=Chinjusha}} of Unkanji Temple, about 500 {{ill|lt=meters|Q11573|WD=Q11573|1=Metre}} to the east, but when the temple was abolished in the first year of {{ill|lt=Meiji|Q3125096|WD=Q3125096|1=Meiji era}}, it was relocated to its present location.

The {{ill|lt=enshrined deity|Q11591100|WD=Q11591100|1=Saijin}} is {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Kikurihime-no-Mikoto|1=UNKNOWN}}.

During the {{ill|lt=Edo period|Q184963|WD=Q184963|1=Edo period}}, it was called {{ill|lt=Hakusan Gongen|Q11579578|WD=Q11579578|1=Hakusan Gongen}} (thought to be associated with {{ill|lt=Hakusan faith|Q11579557|WD=Q11579557|1=Hakusan Faith}}), and in the Meiji period it was known as Nomata Myōjin.

The subsidiary shrine on the left side facing the main hall is the Kasuga Shrine, whose enshrined deity is {{ill|lt=Ame-no-Koyane-no-Mikoto|Q2564508|WD=Q2564508|lt=Ame-no-Koyane-no-Mikoto|1=Ame-no-Koyane}}. Immediately beside it is the Inari Shrine, whose enshrined deity is {{ill|lt=Inari Ōkami|Q719665|WD=Q719665|1=Inari Ōkami}}.

At the offering hall outside the left fence of the shrine buildings, {{ill|lt=Amaterasu Ōmikami|Q455602|WD=Q455602|1=Amaterasu}} and {{ill|lt=Hitokotonushi-no-Kami|Q10864079|WD=Q10864079|lt=Hitokotonushi|1=Hitokotonushi}} are enshrined<ref>{{Cite book|Japanese|editor=Heguri Town History Editorial Committee|title=History of Heguri Town|publisher=Heguri Town Office|date=1976-04|ncid=BN04492478|pages=645-647}}</ref>.

A {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=sacred tree|1=UNKNOWN}} is enshrined within the precincts.

